m\": \"a shame\", \"from\": 790, \"to\": 797}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 844}, {\"ngram\": \"the only capital city\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 884}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 888, \"to\": 897}, {\"ngram\": \"withpolluted waterways\", \"from\": 898, \"to\": 920}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Aside from some malicious disruption of rail and other communications, Paris was spared the crimes and scandals of previous Games.\", \"from\": 922, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 993, \"end\": 998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.34080943561942e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some malicious disruption\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"rail\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"other communications\", \"from\": 971, \"to\": 991}, {\"ngram\": \"the crimes\", \"from\": 1010, \"to\": 1020}, {\"ngram\": \"scandals\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"previous Games\", \"from\": 1037, \"to\": 1051}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is something to be grateful for in a world seemingly trapped incyclesofwarandextremism.\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1143, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 1059, \"to\": 1068}, {\"ngram\": \"a world\", \"from\": 1091, \"to\": 1098}, {\"ngram\": \"seemingly trapped incyclesofwarandextremism\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1142}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, it may be said that the last few weeks have seen the French capital become a beacon of hope intorrid times.\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1260, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1206, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9699152201106868, \"rank\": 0.03068696666504888, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the last few weeks\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1191}, {\"ngram\": \"a beacon\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"hope intorrid times\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1259}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What we saw athletes from all over the world display was that spirit of intense but peaceful competition that was so much a part of the ancient as well as the modern event.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1433, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1273, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"the world display\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"that spirit\", \"from\": 1318, \"to\": 1329}, {\"ngram\": \"intense but peaceful competition\", \"from\": 1333, \"to\": 1365}, {\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 1383, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern event\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1432}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The antagonism of one competitor against another, to the ancient Greeks, implied strife; while competition more as a simple struggle to come first was a virtue.\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1492, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"score\": 0.9999846439747105, \"rank\": 1.535620120486873e-05, \"text\": \"ancient Greeks\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ancient_Greece\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The antagonism\", \"from\": 1435, \"to\": 1449}, {\"ngram\": \"one competitor\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1467}, {\"ngram\": \"another\", \"from\": 1476, \"to\": 1483}, {\"ngram\": \"implied strife\", \"from\": 1508, \"to\": 1522}, {\"ngram\": \"a simple struggle\", \"from\": 1550, \"to\": 1567}, {\"ngram\": \"a virtue\", \"from\": 1586, \"to\": 1594}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And, with some rare exceptions, that same spirit infused those taking part in Paris - fellow athletes embracing one another and celebrating together in mutual respect in a supremely multicultural, multiethnic environment.\", \"from\": 1596, \"to\": 1817, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1674, \"end\": 1679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.34080943561942e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"some rare exceptions\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1626}, {\"ngram\": \"that same spirit\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1644}, {\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1670}, {\"ngram\": \"mutual respect\", \"from\": 1748, \"to\": 1762}, {\"ngram\": \"a supremely multicultural, multiethnic environment\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1816}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were many memorable moments, and most for all the right reasons.\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1889, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many memorable moments\", \"from\": 1830, \"to\": 1852}, {\"ngram\": \"all the right reasons\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1888}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One which particularly stood out - and which went especially viral - was the display put on by the Australian \\\"Raygun\\\" (real name Rachael Gunn), who recalled Great Britain's plucky skier Eddie \\\"the Eagle\\\" Edwards, the sensation of the 1988 Winter Olympics, with her endearingly eclectic breakdancing performance.\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 2202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1989, \"end\": 1999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"score\": 0.9970900802961803, \"rank\": 0.0027961192617808003, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australians\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"score\": 0.9999999987985575, \"rank\": 1.2016151245947933e-09, \"text\": \"Rachael\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Ray\"}, {\"begin\": 2028, \"end\": 2032, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"score\": 0.8780843801772412, \"rank\": 0.13884087954186464, \"text\": \"Gunn\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Gunn\"}, {\"begin\": 2048, \"end\": 2061, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999323440393043, \"rank\": 5.410505256528346e-05, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the display\", \"from\": 1963, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"real name\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2019}, {\"ngram\": \"the sensation\", \"from\": 2104, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1988 Winter Olympics\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2145}, {\"ngram\": \"her endearingly eclectic breakdancing performance\", \"from\": 2152, \"to\": 2201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These days, thanks to the National Lottery, Team GB can look forward to every set of Olympics with the justified expectation of a disproportionately large haul of medals, and Paris has been no exception.\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2407, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2230, \"end\": 2246, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9978072942888118, \"rank\": 0.0021975242181882697, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}, {\"begin\": 2248, \"end\": 2255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999955645842559, \"rank\": 4.420717469331206e-06, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2379, \"end\": 2384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.34080943561942e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"every set\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2285}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympics\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2297}, {\"ngram\": \"the justified expectation\", \"from\": 2303, \"to\": 2328}, {\"ngram\": \"a disproportionately large haul\", \"from\": 2332, \"to\": 2363}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 2367, \"to\": 2373}, {\"ngram\": \"no exception\", \"from\": 2394, \"to\": 2406}]}, {\"sentence\": \"True, the performance has not been quite as strong as at some other recent championships, but the merits of the then prime minister John Major's idea of a national lottery as a way to bypass the difficult politics of funding sport through general taxation have become glitteringly clear.\", \"from\": 2408, \"to\": 2695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2540, \"end\": 2550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.7161193360040608e-28, \"text\": \"John Major\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the performance\", \"from\": 2414, \"to\": 2429}, {\"ngram\": \"some other recent championships\", \"from\": 2465, \"to\": 2496}, {\"ngram\": \"the merits\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2512}, {\"ngram\": \"a national lottery\", \"from\": 2561, \"to\": 2579}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 2583, \"to\": 2588}, {\"ngram\": \"the difficult politics\", \"from\": 2599, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2633, \"to\": 2638}, {\"ngram\": \"general taxation\", \"from\": 2647, \"to\": 2663}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It may even turn out to be the abiding success of his premiership.\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2762, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the abiding success\", \"from\": 2723, \"to\": 2742}, {\"ngram\": \"his premiership\", \"from\": 2746, \"to\": 2761}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FromKeely Hodgkinson in the women's 800m, toKaty Marchant, Emma Finucane and Sophie Capewellin track cycling, toToby Robertsin the climbing, toEmma Hayes leading the US women's football team to gold, there were plenty of outstanding, world-beating achievements.\", \"from\": 2764, \"to\": 3025, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2774, \"end\": 2784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"score\": 0.8270012548371299, \"rank\": 0.20918800806055043, \"text\": \"Hodgkinson\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hodgkinson_Minerals_Area\"}, {\"begin\": 2823, \"end\": 2827, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"score\": 0.9984446170790509, \"rank\": 0.0011727082077224885, \"text\": \"Emma\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emma_Swan\"}, {\"begin\": 2841, \"end\": 2847, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Webster\", \"score\": 0.9875482788743027, \"rank\": 0.007081672808720603, \"text\": \"Sophie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Webster\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sophie_Webster\"}, {\"begin\": 2930, \"end\": 2932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9988508711658742, \"rank\": 0.0011114224744181022, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the women's 800m\", \"from\": 2788, \"to\": 2804}, {\"ngram\": \"toKaty Marchant\", \"from\": 2806, \"to\": 2821}, {\"ngram\": \"track cycling\", \"from\": 2859, \"to\": 2872}, {\"ngram\": \"the climbing\", \"from\": 2891, \"to\": 2903}, {\"ngram\": \"Hayes\", \"from\": 2912, \"to\": 2917}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 2958, \"to\": 2962}, {\"ngram\": \"plenty\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 2981}, {\"ngram\": \"outstanding, world-beating achievements\", \"from\": 2985, \"to\": 3024}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So, Paris was one of the more successful Games, though far from free of controversy.\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3111, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3031, \"end\": 3036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.34080943561942e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the more successful Games\", \"from\": 3048, \"to\": 3073}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3110}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gender status of the Algerian boxer Imane Khelif became arenewed focus for the debate on trans peoplein sport (she isnot trans, as it happens), and, all too predictably, was traduced during one of Donald Trump's tedious, rambling US presidential rallies.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3145, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999747734212721, \"rank\": 2.2552716703652345e-05, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 3152, \"end\": 3164, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 3346, \"end\": 3348, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9988508711658742, \"rank\": 0.0011114224744181022, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gender status\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3129}, {\"ngram\": \"arenewed focus\", \"from\": 3172, \"to\": 3186}, {\"ngram\": \"the debate\", \"from\": 3191, \"to\": 3201}, {\"ngram\": \"trans peoplein sport\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3225}, {\"ngram\": \"Donald Trump\", \"from\": 3313, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Suffice to say, the rows about Khelif confirm how much more work needs to be done to achieve a consensus on chromosomes in sport.\", \"from\": 3371, \"to\": 3500, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the rows\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3395}, {\"ngram\": \"Khelif\", \"from\": 3402, \"to\": 3408}, {\"ngram\": \"how much more work\", \"from\": 3417, \"to\": 3435}, {\"ngram\": \"a consensus\", \"from\": 3464, \"to\": 3475}, {\"ngram\": \"chromosomes\", \"from\": 3479, \"to\": 3490}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 3494, \"to\": 3499}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More broadly, the Games brought the world together.\", \"from\": 3502, \"to\": 3553, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 3516, \"to\": 3525}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3534, \"to\": 3543}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are one of the few events of any kind that are genuinely global, and in troubled times, the modern Olympics serve two complementary roles - distraction and inspiration.\", \"from\": 3554, \"to\": 3727, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the few events\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3584}, {\"ngram\": \"any kind\", \"from\": 3588, \"to\": 3596}, {\"ngram\": \"trouble